{
  "texts": [
    "This was confirmed by further psychological tests that highlighted, on the basis of the ANOVA-MR results, impor-tant interaction effects between the variables \"time\" and \"group\", supporting the hypothesis that certain abilities improved between pre-and post-therapy only for children who also used the BRAVO serious games:",
    "-ability to understand the meaning of sentences with the most diverse grammatical structures, establishing the level of maturity of the receptive grammatical system reached; -selective attention, sustained attention and motor inhibition in a task involving auditory and visual stimuli.",
    "The data obtained are summarised in Table 2.",
    "Virtual reality games made it possible to track the performance of patients on specific parameters agreed with the therapists.",
    "The use of wearable sensors during gaming sessions enabled the collection of biofeedback that could be used to analyse the patient's emotional distress."
  ]
}